  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Business modelling scoping&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This practice describes how to scope your business modelling by defining a set of scoping statements. A set of scoping&#xD;
    statements consisting of the following:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.business.business_modelling_scoping.base_sisas-sintef/workproducts/context_statement_985C5BA2.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_njcVUNa8Ed-d6Ia20mQhAw&quot;>Context statement&lt;/a>, which defines the scope and positions this business model in&#xD;
        its context.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
        href=&quot;./../../../practice.business.business_modelling_scoping.base_sisas-sintef/workproducts/vision_statement_995D28BB.html&quot;&#xD;
         guid=&quot;_5gNc4Na8Ed-d6Ia20mQhAw&quot;>Vision statement&lt;/a>, which describes what to improve, the motivation (i.e. what is&#xD;
        wrong with the current situation), a description or indication of what the improvements might be and a gap&#xD;
        analysis.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
